# Write-read endpoint parity

Every PATCH or POST endpoint that creates or updates a resource must have a corresponding
GET endpoint that retrieves the same data shape.

When adding a new write endpoint:
1. Verify a GET read endpoint exists for the resource at the same path or parent path
2. If no GET exists, add one in the same PR
3. Verify the frontend or client has a function to call the GET endpoint
4. Add an E2E or integration test that writes then reads the resource

Evidence: BUG-2026-05-25-retag-tags-not-visible — `PATCH /documents/{id}/tags` existed
but no `GET /documents/{id}/tags`, so retag results were invisible in the admin UI.

Test: `tests/e2e/test_admin_retag_job.py::test_admin_retag_tags_visible_via_get_endpoint`
